{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":13804,"record_hash":"sha256:7967bf093585ca1b944ab2f9e1bea24c5183933dc3f8cc79a9ff1f2cc28f1f80","timestamp":"2026-05-09T17:20:45.185Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"Yes. In the slim envelope, the human-readable “message” is `content_text`.\n\nFor example:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"event_category\": \"message\",\n  \"role\": \"user\",\n  \"content_text\": \"Please make the checkout flow handle foreign currency.\"\n}\n```\n\nFor assistant messages:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"event_category\": \"message\",\n  \"role\": \"assistant\",\n  \"content_text\": \"I’ll update the pricing calculation and add tests for currency conversion.\"\n}\n```\n\nThe split is:\n\n```text\nevent_category  -> what kind of record is this? message/tool/session/context/other\nrole            -> who said it? user/assistant/system/tool/etc, when known\ncontent_text    -> what was said, in plain normalized text\nsource_record   -> redacted original provider-shaped JSON for provenance/backfill\n```\n\nSo `content_text` is the thing future handoff/UI code would show as the conversation body. `source_record` is the “original evidence,” not the primary display field.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-09T17:20:45.185Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}